The paper discusses the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence in healthcare, specifically in clinical gait analysis. The paper also focuses on the need for transparency and interpretability in AI-based systems, which falls under the category of explainable AI (XAI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
